READ ME

# MERN stack + MySQL Application

// 1. Set up the backend directory and initialize a new Node.js project
	# Make all reference to the Back End folder


// 2. Install the required dependencies (run the following code in the terminal):
<code>npm install express mysql body-parser cors</code>



// 3. Replace 'your_mysql_user', 'your_mysql_password', and 'your_database_name' with your MySQL credentials and database information.



// 4. Initialize React.js project (check BASH code)



// 5. Install Axios to make API requests (run the following code in the terminal):
<code>npm install axios</code>



// 6. Replace the content of src/App.js with code in 'replacement_App.js'



// 7. Start the development server (run the following code in the terminal):
<code>npm start</code>
